Quote: Purau was once plentiful in Canterbury ... It is said to have had roots like clusters of marbles. This is a name scarcely known in Southland.
Notes: c1880 South Island Maori Lists `Wahi Mahika Kai' in 1945 Beattie Maori Place-names of Canterbury 65
